      "writtenOn": "2018-07-20T18:10:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I doubt there\u0027s a way to guarantee it, as recv() could receive a disconnection request, and it needs to disconnect the client. disconnection function frees the client.\n\nYou can check if the |c| is still in the list of clients for the current QemudService and only call sink_reset if it is. But that\u0027s a linked list, and checking on each recv() is quite expensive. An optimization would be to remember the next/prev element in the list before the recv(), and after that check if those still point to |c|",
